Name: Above Operating Range
Description: data valid but above Normal Operating Range reduces the chance of acceptance

Name: Below Daily Detection Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined daily detection limits

Name: Below Detection Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined detection limits

Name: Below Long-term Blank-basd Dt Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined long-term blank based detection limits

Name: Below Method Detection Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined laboratory method detection limits

Name: Below Reporting Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined laboratory reporting limits

Name: Below Sample-specific Detect Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined sample specific detection limits

Name: Below System Detection Limit
Description: data that was found less than defined system detection limits

Name: Between Inst Detect and Quant Limit
Description: between the lowest concentration at which the analyte can not only be reliably detected but at which some predefined goals for bias and imprecision and instrument.

Name: Detected Not Quantified
Description: data that was found and not quanitified within defined laboratory reporting limits or method detection limits

Name: High Moisture
Description: wet and allowed to ferment

Name: Not Detected
Description: data was looked for but was not observed/detected within defined laboratory reporting limits or method detection limits

Name: Not Detected at Detection Limit
Description: Not Detected at Detection Limit

Name: Not Detected at Reporting Limit
Description: Not Detected at Reporting Limit

Name: Not Present
Description: data that was looked for but not found and without laboratory reporting limits or method detection limits http://www.abcwua.org/Substances_Not_Found.aspx

Name: Not Reported
Description: data was collected but not analyzed. (data has not been quantified)

Name: Present Above Quantification Limit
Description: data was found greater than defined laboratory reporting limits or method detection limits. typically for colony count and rare occasions where value is above highest calibration curve point concentration.

Name: Present Below Quantification Limit
Description: data was found less than defined laboratory reporting limits or method detection limits

Name: Reported in Raw Data (attached)
Description: Continuous or time series sampling attached in raw data file

Name: Trace
Description: a very small quantity, especially one too small to be accurately measured.

Name: Unable to Measure
Description: Measurement or sample collection was attempted but unobtainable due to site conditions, equipment failure, or other circumstances

Name: Value Decensored
Description: Value Decensored -  reconstruct or remove the objectionable values of a measurement set

Name: Value affected by contamination
Description: Value affected by contamination as determined for USGS NWIS data; Analyte was detected in both the environmental sample and the associated blanks.

Name: *Non-detect
Description: Hard-coded legacy detection condition
